{
  "text": "The SEM images of the treated and the untreated bacteria showed a clear difference (Figure 3 a-d) ; the untreated bacteria exhibited rod-like structures as in earlier studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The untreated bacteria on the other hand exhibited finer grains or homogeneous surfaces, indicating that the grinding of cells during treatment reduced their size and therefore increased the surface area necessary for effective binding of dyes.",
